A 20-year-old man has been arrested after the body of a woman was found in Hawston in the Western Cape. The woman was found on Friday, with a rope around her neck, said police spokesperson Sergeant Noloyiso Rwexana. "A murder case has been opened for investigation after the body of a 31-year-old woman was found in Cambridge Road," Rwexana said on Sunday. "Police attended to the crime scene at the address and upon their arrival they found the victim with a rope around her neck." The circumstances surrounding the incident were under investigation, Rwexana said. However, a man was arrested and was expected to appear in court on Monday.